		<td><b>Re: Famicom - loading games and reset button.</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Maybe your Famicom has a a slightly glitchy power supply that doesn't settle fast enough? Once the power's already on, the conditions are more stable when you hit reset.<br /><br />As far as bootleg games, the Famicom doesn't have a lockout device, so I don't think there should be a distinction for them like there is for NES.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


